&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Mental Health Nurse&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Seagrove Ward&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;£31,365-£37,890 (Band 6)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Seagrove Ward is a six bed mixed sex Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU); which forms part of the wider mental health acute care pathway within the integrated Isle of Wight NHS Trust. The team aim to provide collaborative and individualised patient care in a safe and therapeutic environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a dedicated and suitably experienced Band 6 Mental Health Nurse to join our supportive nurse led Multi-disciplinary Team. This role will provide clinical leadership and will require excellent shift management skills. You will be required to act as a role model, demonstrating the visions and values of the trust. Provide support to the development of junior staff through supervision and appraisal and ensure that standards of care audited and delivered to a high standard. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will receive a full induction, regular supervision and opportunities for continuing professional development. Seagrove Ward is a member of The Quality Network for Psychiatric Intensive Care Units (QNPICU), and the Reducing Restrictive Practice Programme with the Royal College of Psychiatrists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The right candidate will be imaginative, enthusiastic and able to demonstrate both the drive and motivation to join us on our quality improvement journey.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you wish to discuss this opportunity, please contact Deborah Marshall on (01983) 534074&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
